{{notability|Books|date=January 2016}}
'''''Let There Be Light: Modern Cosmology and Kabbalah, a New Conversation Between Science and Religion''''' is a book by [[Howard Alan Smith|Howard Smith]], an [[astrophysicist]]. The book, published in 2006, was written for the layperson. It discusses using simple language basic concepts in modern [[cosmology]] and [[Kabbalah]] (a form of Jewish mysticism), the creation of the universe [[Ex nihilo|from nothing]] via the [[big bang]], [[general relativity]], [[dark matter]], cosmic acceleration, [[quantum mechanics]], and [[free will]], among other topics. The book attempts to clearly explains these subjects, and uses them to try to illustrate how religion and science together can enrich one's spiritual and intellectual life.

