'''''Philosophy, Theory, and Practice in Biology''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[open access]] [[academic journal]] covering [[mathematical biology|mathematical]] and [[theoretical biology]], as well as their [[philosophy|philosophical]] underpinnings. It was established as '''''Philosophy & Theory in Biology''''', obtaining its current name in January 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.philsci.org/announcements/other-recent-announcements/1137-january-2017-relaunching-of-philosophy-theory-in-biology-as-philosophy-theory-and-practice-in-biology.html |title=January 2017: Relaunching "Philosophy & Theory in Biology" as "Philosophy, Theory, and Practice in Biology" |last=Lipman |first=Sarah |website=www.philsci.org |language=en-gb |access-date=2017-08-04}}</ref> It is published by [[Michigan Publishing]] and the [[executive editor]] is Christopher Eliot ([[Hofstra University]]).
